---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="CyberInventors exists to spotlight the women building the future of cybersecurity."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white">About CyberInventors</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc mt-10 max-w-none">
      <p>
        CyberInventors is a directory built around a single conviction: the women
        founding and leading cybersecurity companies deserve to be seen. Not as a
        footnote. Not in a sidebar labeled "diversity." Front and center.
      </p>

      <h2>Why We Exist</h2>
      <p>
        Women make up roughly 24% of the cybersecurity workforce — and a far
        smaller fraction of its founders. When coverage of the industry appears,
        it almost always centers the product, the funding round, or the
        company name. The person who built it, and the journey that got them
        there, rarely leads the story.
      </p>
      <p>
        CyberInventors flips that. Every profile starts with the founder.
        The company comes second.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Founder directory</strong> — a curated, searchable index of
          women founders and senior leaders in cybersecurity, linked to the
          companies they built.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>News feed</strong> — aggregated coverage from across the
          security media landscape, surfacing stories about these founders and
          their work as they happen.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Submissions</strong> — anyone can nominate a founder or
          company for inclusion. We review every submission.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who We Include</h2>
      <p>
        We cover women who founded or co-founded a cybersecurity company, as
        well as senior women leaders (C-suite, VP) who are driving meaningful
        technical or strategic work at security-focused organizations. We focus
        on:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Founders at any stage — from pre-seed through public</li>
        <li>Companies solving real security problems with real customers</li>
        <li>Leaders with demonstrated domain expertise, not just titles</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Submit a Founder or Company</h2>
      <p>
        Know someone who should be here?{" "}
        <a href="/submit">Submit them</a> and we'll review it for inclusion.
        Self-nominations welcome.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
